5 SECTION 64, IS AMENDED TO READ AS FOLLOWS [EFFECTIVE
6 JULY 1, 2026]: Sec. 10.5. (a) A person less than twenty-one (21) years
7 of age who:
8 (1) purchases a tobacco product or vapor product;
9 (2) accepts a tobacco product or vapor product for personal use;
10 or
11 (3) possesses a tobacco product or vapor product on the person's
12 person;
13 commits a Class C infraction.
14 (b) It is a defense under subsection (a) that the accused person acted
15 in the ordinary course of employment in a business concerning a
16 tobacco product or vapor product for the following activities:
17 (1) Agriculture.
18 (2) Processing.
19 (3) Transporting.
20 (4) Wholesaling.
21 (5) Retailing.
22 (c) A person less than twenty-one (21) years of age who has in the
23 person's possession false or fraudulent evidence of majority or identity
24 with the intent to purchase a tobacco product or vapor product
25 commits a Class C infraction.
